\ Scalar/matrix broadcasting through the polymorphic + - * / primitives.
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 10 + .
[ 10 20 30 40 ] 2 2 matrix 5 - .
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 3 * .
[ 10 20 30 40 ] 2 2 matrix 10 / .
[ 1 2 ] 1 2 matrix 0 + .
[ 1 2 3 ] 1 3 matrix 0 * .
\ scalar on the left broadcasts too
10 [ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix + .
100 [ 10 20 30 40 ] 2 2 matrix - .

\ Vector broadcasting: a dimension of size 1 stretches to match the other.
\ a column vector (n x 1) broadcasts across the columns
[ 1 2  3 4 ] 2 2 matrix  [ 10 20 ] 2 1 matrix  + .   \ [[11 12][23 24]]
[ 1 2  3 4 ] 2 2 matrix  [ 10 20 ] 2 1 matrix  * .   \ row-scaling -> [[10 20][60 80]]
\ a row vector (1 x k) broadcasts down the rows
[ 1 2  3 4 ] 2 2 matrix  [ 10 20 ] 1 2 matrix  + .   \ [[11 22][13 24]]
[ 1 2  3 4 ] 2 2 matrix  [ 2 3 ] 1 2 matrix  * .     \ [[2 6][6 12]]
\ order matters for the non-commutative ops
[ 100 200 ] 2 1 matrix  [ 1 2  3 4 ] 2 2 matrix  - .   \ col - A -> [[99 98][197 196]]
[ 1 2  3 4 ] 2 2 matrix  [ 100 200 ] 2 1 matrix  - .   \ A - col -> [[-99 -98][-197 -196]]
\ a 1x1 matrix broadcasts exactly like a scalar
[ 5 ] 1 1 matrix  [ 1 2  3 4 ] 2 2 matrix  + .         \ [[6 7][8 9]]
\ shapes that don't conform error
[ 1 2 3 ] 3 1 matrix  [ 1 2  3 4 ] 2 2 matrix  + .     \ error: 3x1 vs 2x2

clear
\ ---- scalar cases ----
5 abs .
-5 abs .
0 abs .
-3.14 abs .
4 sqrt .
9 sqrt .
0 sqrt .
1 sqrt .
0 exp .
1 exp .
1 log .
0 sin .
0 cos .
0 tan .
0 tanh .

\ ---- matrix cases (element-wise) ----
[ -1 2 -3 4 ] 2 2 matrix abs .
[ 1 4 9 16 ] 2 2 matrix sqrt .
[ 0 1 ] 1 2 matrix exp .
[ 1 ] 1 1 matrix log .
[ 0 0 0 0 ] 2 2 matrix sin .
[ 0 0 0 0 ] 2 2 matrix cos .
[ 0 0 ] 1 2 matrix tanh .
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 1+ .
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 1- .
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix sq .

\ ---- compositions ----
4 sqrt 2 = .
1 exp ln .
[ 1 4 9 16 25 ] 1 5 matrix sqrt .

\ ---- failures ----
"x" abs
"x" sqrt
< 1 2 > exp

clear
\ round (nearest, half away from zero), round-up (ceil), round-down (floor),
\ truncate (toward zero). All polymorphic over floats and matrices.

\ ---- round ----
2.4 round .          \ 2
2.5 round .          \ 3
2.6 round .          \ 3
-2.4 round .         \ -2
-2.5 round .         \ -3
3.0 round .          \ 3

\ ---- round-up (ceil) ----
2.1 round-up .       \ 3
2.0 round-up .       \ 2
-2.9 round-up .      \ -2

\ ---- round-down (floor) ----
2.9 round-down .     \ 2
2.0 round-down .     \ 2
-2.1 round-down .    \ -3

\ ---- truncate (toward zero) ----
2.9 truncate .       \ 2
-2.9 truncate .      \ -2
-0.5 truncate .      \ 0

\ ---- polymorphic over matrices (element-wise) ----
[ 1.2 2.7 -1.5 -2.8 ] 2 2 matrix round .       \ [1 3 -2 -3]
[ 1.2 2.7 -1.5 ] 1 3 matrix round-up .         \ [2 3 -1]
[ 1.2 2.7 -1.5 ] 1 3 matrix round-down .       \ [1 2 -2]
[ 1.9 -1.9 ] 1 2 matrix truncate .             \ [1 -1]

\ ---- failure ----
"x" round

clear
\ asin, acos, atan — polymorphic over floats and matrices.

\ ---- asin ----
0 asin .             \ 0
1 asin .             \ 1.5708   (pi/2)
-1 asin .            \ -1.5708

\ ---- acos ----
1 acos .             \ 0
0 acos .             \ 1.5708   (pi/2)
-1 acos .            \ 3.14159  (pi)

\ ---- atan ----
0 atan .             \ 0
1 atan .             \ 0.785398 (pi/4)
-1 atan .            \ -0.785398

\ ---- round trip ----
1 atan tan .         \ 1

\ ---- polymorphic over a matrix ----
[ 0 1 ] 1 2 matrix atan .       \ [0 0.785398]

\ ---- a float result that would be NaN is null: falsy, none?, = null ----
-1 sqrt . cr
-1 sqrt null = . cr
: nan-is-falsy -1 sqrt if 1 else 0 then ;
nan-is-falsy . cr
[ 3 -1 1 ] 3 1 matrix ln 1 0 @i,j none? . cr

\ ---- failure ----
"x" asin
